$ NastAero VM5: Three-Bar Truss (Plane Truss)
$ Reference: MSC Nastran Verification Manual - classic 3-bar truss
$ Three rods meeting at node 4, loaded with Fx=1000, Fy=-1000
$ All rods: A=1.0 in^2, E=10e6 psi
$
$ Rod 1: node 1(0,40) to 4(0,0), length=40 in (vertical)
$ Rod 2: node 2(40,40) to 4(0,0), length=40*sqrt(2) in (diagonal)
$ Rod 3: node 3(40,0) to 4(0,0), length=40 in (horizontal)
$
$ Analytical (direct stiffness):
$ ux = 0.004 in, uy = -0.004 in
$
SOL 101
CEND
TITLE = VM5 - THREE BAR TRUSS
SPC = 1
LOAD = 1
DISPLACEMENT(PRINT) = ALL
SPCFORCES(PRINT) = ALL
BEGIN BULK
$
GRID,1,,0.0,40.0,0.0
GRID,2,,40.0,40.0,0.0
GRID,3,,40.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,0.0,0.0
$
$ Use CROD elements (axial-only, no bending)
CROD,1,1,1,4
CROD,2,1,2,4
CROD,3,1,3,4
$
PROD,1,1,1.0
MAT1,1,10.0e6,,0.3,0.0
$
$ Pin supports at nodes 1, 2, 3 (all 6 DOFs)
SPC1,1,123456,1,2,3
$ Constrain out-of-plane DOFs at node 4 (planar truss in XY plane)
SPC1,1,3456,4
$
$ Forces at node 4: Fx=+1000 lb, Fy=-1000 lb
FORCE,1,4,,1000.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
FORCE,2,4,,1000.0,0.0,-1.0,0.0
$
$ Use LOAD combination to combine both forces
LOAD,1,1.0,1.0,1,1.0,2
$
ENDDATA
